eader":true,"content":"Watermelon gazpacho"},{"content":"Place watermelon, onion, capsicum, cucumber, garlic, vinegar and oil into mixing bowl and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Add mint, parsley, basil, ice cubes, salt and pepper and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a bowl and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 1 hour before serving."},{"content":"Drizzle with jalapeño oil and garnish with diced cucumber and extra sliced basil before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Store leftover oil in a dark, cool place. Drizzle over bruschetta or poached eggs for a bit of heat. Or make your own salsa and use in place of olive oil and\/or chillies.","To make this recipe suitable for a raw food diet, simply omit the jalapeño oil."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}